  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/6248",
  "title": "Installation problem: Cannot find type definition file for 'googlemaps'",
  "body": "### 🐛 Current behavior\r\n\r\nInstantsearch.js/es/widgets/geo-search/geosearch.d.ts and Instantsearch.js/es/widgets/geo-search/createHTMLMarker.d.ts both have the following line of code: \r\nLine 2: `/// <reference types=\"googlemaps\" />`\r\nMy IDE gives the following error regarding that line: \"Cannot find type definition file for 'googlemaps'\" and Angular will give me the same error during an ng serve.\r\n\r\nIf I attempt to install @types/googlemaps to solve the issue, every declaration it has in common with @types/google.maps get a Duplicate Identifier error. \r\n\r\nRemoving the line fixes the issue as a workaround, but it won't be applicable in production. \r\nThis line is also not in your source code, which I'll assume it is generated by something.\r\n\r\n\r\n### 🔍 Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nSimply download the relevant libraries, start a basic angular project and attempt to launch the front end.\r\nI am sorry, I have not been able to run the codesandbox online, but it worked locally.\r\n\r\n### Live reproduction\r\n\r\nhttps://codesandbox.io/p/github/Annoxis/instantsearch_googlemaps_import_problem/main?file=%2Fmy-angular-app%2Fpackage-lock.json&workspaceId=7fae891e-38f3-4e2e-9b6a-9d119ae163ab\r\n\r\n### 💭 Expected behavior\r\n\r\nMy front end compile.\r\n\r\n### Package version\r\n\r\nInstantsearch.js 4.72.1, types/google.maps 3.55.9, angular 17.3.4, npm 10.5.0\r\n\r\n### Operating system\r\n\r\nTested under Mac Sonoma and Windows 11 (WSL 2)\r\n\r\n### Browser\r\n\r\nIrrelevant\r\n\r\n### Code of Conduct\r\n\r\n- [x] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct",
